[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     10[0m:[38;5;10m[49m pip install boto3 pydicom numpy
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     11[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     12[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     13[0m:[38;5;10m[49m `pydicom` handles DICOM metadata parsing. `numpy` handles pixel array manipulation for preprocessing. The actual model inference happens on SageMaker endpoints; you don't need TensorFlow or PyTorch locally.
